cast.overview: In 19th century France, Jean Valjean, a man imprisoned for stealing bread, must flee a relentless policeman named Javert. The pursuit consumes both men's lives, and soon Valjean finds himself in the midst of the student revolutions in France.
cast.title: Les Misérables

details.biography: Reine Brynolfsson (born 15 January 1953) is a Swedish actor. He was born in Gothenburg. He started his career as a theatre actor. He is known for acting in several films by director Colin Nutley.
details.name: Reine Brynolfsson
details.place_of_birth: Göteborg, Göteborg- och Bohus län, Sweden
